<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<xsl:stylesheet version="1.1"
	xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format"
	exclude-result-prefixes="fo" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions"
	xmlns:java="java">

	<xsl:template match="/" name="LPL-AMEND-AK">

		<fo:block>
			<xsl:call-template name="CommonHeader" />
		</fo:block>

		<fo:block text-align="center" margin-left="1.3in"
			margin-right="1.3in" font-size="12px"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			space-before="5mm" space-after="5mm" font-weight="bold">
			ALASKA AMENDATORY ENDORSEMENT
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block padding-left="5pt"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			font-size="10px" text-align="justify">

			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
				In consideration of the premium charged, it is agreed that:
			</fo:block>

			<fo:block space-after="4mm">


				<fo:list-block>
					<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
						<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								<fo:inline>1.</fo:inline>
							</fo:block>
						</fo:list-item-label>
						<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
							<fo:block space-after="4mm">
								Section III, Extension of Coverage D., Extended Reporting Period
								Extensions, is amended as follows:
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block>
								<fo:list-block>
									<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
										<fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:block>a.</fo:block>
										</fo:list-item-label>
										<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
											<fo:block>
												Subsection 1., Automatic Extended Reporting Period, is amended by
												deletion of the phrase “or for nonpayment of Deductible due
												hereunder”.
											</fo:block>
										</fo:list-item-body>
									</fo:list-item>
									<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
										<fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:block>b.</fo:block>
										</fo:list-item-label>
										<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
											<fo:block>
												Subsection 2., Optional Extended Reporting Period, is amended by
												deletion of the phrase “or for the nonpayment of Deductible
												due
												hereunder”.
											</fo:block>
										</fo:list-item-body>
									</fo:list-item>
									<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
										<fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:block>c.</fo:block>
										</fo:list-item-label>
										<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
											<fo:block>
												Subsection 2., Optional Extended Reporting Period, paragraphs (a)
												through (e) are deleted and replaced with the following:
											</fo:block>
											<fo:block>
											<fo:list-block>
											<fo:list-item>
											<fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:block>
												(a)
											</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
												<fo:block>12 months for a premium charge of 100% of the annual policy premium;</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-body>
											</fo:list-item>
											<fo:list-item>
											<fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:block>
												(b)
											</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
												<fo:block>36 months for a premium charge of 185% of the annual policy premium;</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-body>
											</fo:list-item>
											<fo:list-item>
											<fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:block>
												(c)
											</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
												<fo:block>60 months for a premium charge of 200% of the annual policy premium;</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-body>
											</fo:list-item>
											</fo:list-block>
											</fo:block>
										</fo:list-item-body>
									</fo:list-item>
									<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
										<fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:block>d.</fo:block>
										</fo:list-item-label>
										<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
											<fo:block>
												Subsection 3., Non-Practicing Extended Reporting Period, subsection
												(b), Non-Practicing Extended Reporting Period Premium and Deductible,
												is amended by deleting the phrase “300% of the individual lawyer
												<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured’s</fo:inline> proportionate share of the annual policy premium” and
												replacing it with “200% of the individual lawyer <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured’s</fo:inline>
												proportionate share of the annual policy premium”.
											</fo:block>
										</fo:list-item-body>
									</fo:list-item>
									<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
										<fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:block>e.</fo:block>
										</fo:list-item-label>
										<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
											<fo:block space-after="4mm">
												Subsection 4., Conditions for Extended Reporting Periods, is deleted
												and replaced with the following:
											</fo:block>
											<fo:block>
											<fo:list-block>
											<fo:list-item>
											<fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:block font-weight="bold">
												4.
											</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
											<fo:block font-weight="bold" space-after="4mm">
												Conditions for Extended Reporting Periods
											</fo:block>
											<fo:block>
											<fo:list-block>
											<fo:list-item>
											<fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:block></fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
												<fo:block>As a condition precedent to the right to elect an Extended Reporting Period:</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-body>
											</fo:list-item>
											<fo:list-item>
											<fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:block>(a)</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
												<fo:block>all <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insureds</fo:inline> must be in compliance with the terms and conditions of the policy;
												</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-body>
											</fo:list-item>
											<fo:list-item>
											<fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:block>(b)</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
												<fo:block>the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured’s</fo:inline> right to practice law has not been revoked,
												suspended or surrendered at the request of any regulatory authority for
												reasons other than death, disability or retirement; and
												</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-body>
											</fo:list-item>
											<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
											<fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:block>(c)</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
												<fo:block>the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> provides the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> with written notice of its
												selection and pays the premium charge, and any other monies due and
												owing the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>, if applicable, for the selected Extended Reporting
												Period in full within 60 days of the expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>.
												</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-body>
											</fo:list-item>
											<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
											<fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:block></fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-label>
											<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
												<fo:block>This right to elect an Extended Reporting Period shall lapse unless the
												provisions of (a) through (c) in the preceding paragraph are fully met.</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-body>
											</fo:list-item>
											</fo:list-block>
											</fo:block>
											</fo:list-item-body>
											</fo:list-item>
											</fo:list-block>
											</fo:block>
										</fo:list-item-body>
									</fo:list-item>
								</fo:list-block>
							</fo:block>
						</fo:list-item-body>
					</fo:list-item>
					<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
					<fo:list-item-label>
						<fo:block>2.</fo:block>
					</fo:list-item-label>
					<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
						<fo:block>
							Section VI., General Condition B., Defense and Settlement, paragraph 1., is amended by deletion of the last sentence.
						</fo:block>
					</fo:list-item-body>
					</fo:list-item>
					<fo:list-item space-after="7mm">
					<fo:list-item-label>
						<fo:block>3.</fo:block>
					</fo:list-item-label>
					<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
						<fo:block space-after="4mm">
							Section VI., General Condition C., Action Against <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>, is amended by addition of the following:
						</fo:block>
						<fo:block>
						<fo:list-block>
						<fo:list-item>
						<fo:list-item-label>
						<fo:block>
							•
						</fo:block>
						</fo:list-item-label>
						<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
						<fo:block>
							An <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured</fo:inline> has three years to bring an action against the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>.
							Such time limitation begins to run only after there has been a breach
							of contract such as a denial of a <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Claim</fo:inline> or failure to defend.
						</fo:block>
						</fo:list-item-body>
						</fo:list-item>
						</fo:list-block>
						</fo:block>
					</fo:list-item-body>
					</fo:list-item>
					<fo:list-item>
					<fo:list-item-label>
					<fo:block>4.</fo:block>
					</fo:list-item-label>
					<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
					<fo:block>
						Section VI., General Condition D., Cancellation and Nonrenewal, is deleted and replaced with the following:
					</fo:block>
					</fo:list-item-body>
					</fo:list-item>
				</fo:list-block>
			</fo:block>
			<fo:block margin-top="2.5cm"/>
           <fo:block  font-size="9px" color="grey" text-align="left">LPL-AMEND-AK (04/17)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Page 1 of 3</fo:block>
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block break-after="page" />
		<fo:block padding-left="5pt"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			font-size="10px" text-align="justify">
		
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label start-indent="7mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			D.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold" space-after="4mm">
			Cancellation, Nonrenewal and Conditional Renewal
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			1.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold" space-after="4mm">
			Cancellation
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(a)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> may cancel this policy at any time prior to the
			expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline> by providing prior written notice
			to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or by surrender of this policy to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or its
			authorized agent. If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> cancels this policy, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
			shall return or credit 92.5% of the unearned portion of the premium to
			the agent or broker of record, or directly to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> or
			premium finance company, if applicable, within 45 days of receipt of
			the request for cancellation or the effective date of cancellation,
			whichever is later.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(b)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> may only cancel this policy for nonpayment of premium.
			This policy may be canceled by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> by mailing to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named
			Insured</fo:inline> at its last known address, and to the agent or broker of
			record, written notice of cancellation at least 20 days before the
			effective date of cancellation. Such notice shall include the reason
			for the cancellation. The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall mail the notice by first-class
			mail and obtain a certificate of mailing from the U.S. Postal Service,
			or transmit the notice by electronic means to the last known electronic
			address of the intended recipient, if the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> can obtain an
			electronic confirmation of receipt. The effective date of cancellation
			stated in such notice shall become the expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy
			Period</fo:inline>. If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> cancels this policy, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall return or
			credit the pro rata unearned premium to the agent or broker of record,
			or directly to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> or premium finance company, if
			applicable. Payment or tender of any unearned premium by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
			shall not be a condition precedent to the effectiveness of
			cancellation, but such payment shall be made within 45 days after
			notice of cancellation is given.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			2.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold" space-after="4mm">
			Nonrenewal
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			This policy may be nonrenewed by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> by mailing to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named
			Insured</fo:inline> at its last known address, and to the agent or broker of
			record, written notice of nonrenewal at least 45 days prior to the
			expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>. The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall mail the notice
			by first-class mail and obtain a certificate of mailing from the U.S.
			Postal Service, or transmit the notice by electronic means to the last
			known electronic address of the intended recipient, if the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> can
			obtain an electronic confirmation of receipt. If notice of nonrenewal
			is not given as required, the existing policy shall continue until the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> provides notice for the required time period. However, this
			shall not apply:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>(a)</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			if the Insurer has in good faith manifested its willingness to renew;
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>(b)</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			in case of nonpayment of premium for the expiring policy; or
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>(c)</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			if the Named Insured fails to pay the premium as required by the Insurer for renewal.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">3.</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			Conditional Renewal
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
			If the renewal premium is increased more than 10% for a reason other
			than an increase in coverage or exposure base, or if after renewal
			there will be a material restriction or reduction in coverage not
			specifically requested by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, written notice shall be
			mailed to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> at its last known address, and to the agent
			or broker of record, at least 45 days before the expiration date of the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>. The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall mail the notice by first-class mail
			and obtain a certificate of mailing from the U.S. Postal Service, or
			transmit the notice by electronic means to the last known electronic
			address of the intended recipient, if the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> can obtain an
			electronic confirmation of receipt. If notice before expiration of the
			policy is not given as required, the existing policy shall continue
			until the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> provides notice for the required time period.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			5.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			Section VI., General Condition H., Other Insurance, is deleted and replaced with the following:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			H.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold" space-after="4mm">
			Other Insurance
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
			All Damages and Defense Expenses payable under this policy shall
			contribute with other existing insurance, unless such other insurance
			is written specifically excess of this policy. The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall not be
			liable under this policy for a greater proportion of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Damages</fo:inline> and
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Defense Expenses</fo:inline> than the applicable Limit of Liability under this
			policy bears to the total applicable limits of liability of all valid
			and collectible insurance. This policy shall not be subject to the
			terms or conditions of any other insurance.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block margin-top="2cm"/>
